                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           The note is written in the main hand. It contains the names of the donor Walda Māryām, as well as his father Gabra Wahǝd, his mother Walatta ʾAnanya and the older variant of the church name, i.e., Qärnä Säbär.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The names of the donors and nomina sacra are sometimes written in the supplication formulas, in a secondary hand: <locus target="17vb">17vb</locus>, 22rab, 28ra, 31ra, 32ra, 78rb).&#xD;
- Writing exercises and doodles: <locus target="1r">1r</locus>, 11v, 12r, 25v, 39v, 46v, 47r, 61r, 84r, 96rv.</item>
                     </list>
